CONCLUSIONS: Causal-modeling techniques, each subject to diﬀerent assumptions, demonstrated causal eﬀects of locally generated pollutants on daily deaths with eﬀects at concentrations below the current EPA daily PM2:5 standard. https://doi.org/10.1289/EHP2732},
